messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Explanation:
- The printDocument method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printdocument", method = RequestMethod.POST). There is no class-level @RequestMapping that would add a prefix, so the full path is exactly "/printdocument".
- The method attribute explicitly specifies RequestMethod.POST, so only POST is allowed by the code. There are no annotations in this controller that declare HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE or PATCH for the same "/printdocument" path.
- I did not assume framework-injected behavior (e.g., automatic handling of OPTIONS or HEAD); the decisions above are strictly based on the source code annotations.
